+Create the sending endpoint in either the main process or the renderer process.
+Create a matching receiving endpoint in the peer process with
+`SharedMemory.acceptChannel` and the same channel `name`. When the sending
+endpoint is created in the main process, Electron delivers channel wakeups to the
+renderer frame that was used to create `pool`.
 
 When `copyFallback` is omitted or set to `throw`, and no ring slot options are
 provided, this method does not allocate copy-fallback ring storage. This is the
@@ -85,14 +87,16 @@ Returns `SharedMemoryChannel` - The sending channel endpoint.
